value.0: The guard eyes you warily as you approach. He seems jumpy and on edge. "What be your business in Brogan's Arm?" he musters, glancing over your shoulder to search the shadows beyond.
The dwarf hesitates for a moment, wary that your question might ensnare him. He chooses his words with care. "I be down in the mines, working, at the time..."
"Word is that a large group passed through, however, heading north. Not sure what they could have been up to but that be Guild business, not me own."
The dwarf tenses at your words but says nothing. He and his fellow armsman exchange meaningful glances.
"Aye. Master Jager's closed down the mine where I usually work and the Council says we're to guard the south gate instead. No one passes in or out." The man's eyes dart about nervously.
The man grunts. "Dunno. I showed up in the morning and Master Jager had a note posted to the door. We've had... troubles in the past."
"Nothing," he says, deliberately avoiding your gaze. "If ye want to know, you go read the exhibits in the Guild Hall. That be Council-approved and I'll not say a word to contradict it."
He squints at you, suspicious. "That be the south road, the only way out of the mountains. The only way to stand where you be standing and not have passed that way is to be Brogan-born."
"Ain't nothing the matter," growls the dwarf. "Now move along."
The guard gives you an irritated scowl. "Move along, now. I have a job to do and ye be distracting me from it."
"Have any strangers come through town lately?"
